# 🧠 BFF – Terminal Assistant CLI

`BFF` is a command-line tool that helps you generate bash commands and answer terminal-related questions using a local or remote LLM backend like [Ollama](https://ollama.com). It’s designed for developers and power users who want fast, accurate command-line assistance directly in their terminal.

---

## 🚀 Features

- 🧑‍💻 Generate bash commands from natural language prompts
- 🔍 Get answers to general terminal and shell questions
- ⚡️ Fast, streaming responses from your local or remote LLM
- 🔧 Built with [Cobra](https://github.com/spf13/cobra) for robust CLI support
- 🛠 Easily extensible for new commands and workflows

---

## 🛠 Installation

### Clone and build

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/terminal-assistant.git
cd terminal-assistant
make build
mv bin/bff ~/.local/bin/
echo 'export PATH="$HOME/.local/bin:$PATH"' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
```

### Set environment variables

```bash
export OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434
export OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.2
```

---

## 📝 Usage

Ask a general terminal question:
```bash
bff -q "How do I list all files including hidden ones?"
```

Ask for a command suggestion:
```bash
bff -c "List all .go files recursively"
```

### Flags

| Flag         | Alias | Description                                 |
| ------------ | ----- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `--command`  | `-c`  | Ask for a bash command suggestion           |
| `--question` | `-q`  | Ask a general terminal or shell question    |
| `--help`     | `-h`  | Show help message (auto-generated by Cobra) |

---

## 🗂 Project Structure

- `main.go` – Entry point for the CLI
- `cmd/` – Cobra command definitions
- `internal/ollama/` – LLM integration and helpers

